 V4-1  DUPLICATE BuildSphereVis WITH `part` TYPO
        v4 shipped two function definitions with the same name.  The
        first used `s.Adornee = part` (undefined variable, runtime error
        on first call).  The second correct definition overrode it in
        Lua's scoping, masking the error — but the dead code was still
        parsed and allocated.  Fix: single correct definition only.

 V4-2  Stats.WhitelistHits COUNTED PER-FRAME
        The heartbeat incremented WhitelistHits every tick (~60/s) for
        every whitelisted player in range.  One friend standing still for
        one minute = 3600 "hits".  The stat was meaningless.
        Fix: `WLInRangePrev[uid]` set — increment only on 0→1 transition
        (player just entered range), not while they remain in range.

 V4-3  CONCURRENT FetchWhitelist RACE
        Clicking REFRESH while a fetch was in progress spawned a second
        concurrent fetch.  Both could write to `Whitelist` and
        `WhitelistCount` at overlapping points.
        Fix: `isFetching` boolean guard; REFRESH no-ops if already
        in progress, and shows "Loading..." on the button.

 V4-4  wlStatusLabel NIL DURING INITIAL FETCH
        `task.spawn(FetchWhitelist)` was called BEFORE `BuildGUI()`, so
        `wlStatusLabel` was nil when the fetch wrote "Loading..." and
        "Loaded N ids" to it.  Initial status updates were silently
        dropped.
        Fix: BuildGUI() called first; task.spawn(FetchWhitelist) after.

 V4-5  AP() CLOSURE ALLOCATED EVERY HEARTBEAT
        Despite v4 claiming to fix "ArcPoint closure allocation every
        frame" (fix #6), `AP` was still defined as `local function AP(i)`
        INSIDE UpdateArcVis — a new closure capturing 5 upvalues on every
        Heartbeat call.  The fix comment was wrong.
        Fix: AP fully inlined — its 3-component computation is written
        directly in the loop body.  Zero function allocations.

 V4-6  ARC COLOR WRITTEN EVERY FRAME
        `ArcPool[i].Color = col` was set on all 16 parts every Heartbeat
        even when the color hadn't changed.  Color3 property writes are
        not free — each triggers a Roblox engine property-changed path.
        Fix: `lastArcColor` dirty flag; skip all color writes when the
        state hasn't changed.

 V4-7  SPHERE COLOR WRITTEN EVERY FRAME
        Same issue: `VisSphere.Color3` and `VisSphere.SurfaceColor3`
        written every tick.
        Fix: `lastSphereColor` dirty flag alongside the existing
        `lastSphereSize` flag.

 V4-8  IsTeammate READS LocalPlayer.Team EVERY CALL
        `LocalPlayer.Team` was property-accessed once per player per
        Heartbeat (up to ~99 reads/tick in a full server).
        Fix: `cachedLocalTeam` local updated on `Team` property change
        signal.  IsTeammate reads the cache — zero property accesses.

 V4-9  UIS GLOBAL LISTENERS REGISTERED INSIDE BuildGUI
        `UIS.InputEnded` and `UIS.InputChanged` were connected inside
        BuildGUI().  If BuildGUI were called again they would accumulate.
        Neither was stored in `Connections`, so Kill never disconnected
        them.  Window drag state (`dragging`, `dStart`, `wStart`) were
        BuildGUI-local closures — multiple registrations would race.
        Fix: the two UIS listeners are registered exactly once at module
        level, stored in Connections, and reference module-level drag
        state.  Window drag state extracted to module-level variables.

 V4-10 arcAngleDirty TRIGGERED BY SIZE CHANGE (INCORRECT)
        The Size slider set `arcAngleDirty = true`.  ArcAngles holds
        (cos, sin) pairs for angular offsets — it contains no Size data.
        The redundant rebuild wasted ~0.3ms per size-slider drag tick.
        Fix: Size change never touches arcAngleDirty.  Arc geometry uses
        the live `CFG.Size` value for reach at draw time; no rebuild needed.

 V4-11 WhitelistHits NOT RESET ON WHITELIST REFRESH
        Fetching a new whitelist didn't clear the hit counter, leaving
        stale counts from the old list in the stats strip.
        Fix: Stats.WhitelistHits = 0 at the start of each successful
        FetchWhitelist parse.

